Comment.val: /*Adds a chargedServiceFee block (CFB) AND/OR a productFeeSettingConfiguration block (PFSB) to the XML. The ServiceFeeData starts with zero or more CFBs followed by zero or more PFSBs. If max one CFB is added, the PFSB can be added within the same run. When more than one CFBs are added the corresponding PFSBs are added in a second run.*/

Text.val: When the new style calculation (s_UseNewStyleServiceFeeCalc) was NOT used, there won't be any SERVICEFEE_HDR records for the
given period. Since in this case the PPR_ID of the payer and the PPR_ID of the calculation are the same both events will be used
When the new style calculation was used and only one product was found, the ProductFeeSettingConfigurationXML can be added
If the calculation of the payer wasn't found, the payer still could have had old style calculations in the given period hence
add the chargedXML and productFeeSettingConfigurationXMl of the payer when present:
Always add the ProductFeeSettingConfigXML of the child calculation:
When more than one product was found a second run is necessary:
If the calculation of the payer wasn't found, the payer still could have had old style calculations in the given period hence
add the chargedXML of the payer when present:
Adding productFeeSettingConfigurationXML of the old style calculations of the payer only when chargedXML was added for the payer
